abstract: Less than two weeks after an anti-capitalist campaign descended on the London cathedral as part of the Occupy London Stock Exchange movement, the Rev. Giles Fraser has resigned over plans to forcibly remove the protesters.
snippet: Less than two weeks after an anti-capitalist campaign descended on the London cathedral as part of the Occupy London Stock Exchange movement, the Rev. Giles Fraser has resigned over plans to forcibly remove the protesters.
lead_paragraph: Less than two weeks after an anti-capitalist campaign descended on St. Paul's Cathedral in London as part of the Occupy London Stock Exchange movement, the church's chancellor, the Rev. Giles Fraser, has resigned over plans to forcibly remove the protesters.

headline.main: St. Paul's Chancellor Quits Over Plans to Remove Protesters
